parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of Takata airbags can cause serious injuries or fatalities due to improper deployment or lack of deployment in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy or deploy improperly
debris from airbag deployment causes injuries
airbag inflators have crude cut-out circles at the end of wires

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unavailability of Replacement Parts for Takata Airbag Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of replacement parts for the Takata airbag recall can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, putting drivers and passengers at risk of serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: Dealerships unable to schedule appointments for recall repairs due to part unavailability
customers unable to get through to customer service
lack of communication from manufacturer or dealership.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Trailing Arm Separation Due to Frame Rust
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the rear trailing arm from the frame can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: appearance of the vehicle being lifted

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Spongy or Extending to Floor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A spongy or extending brake pedal can cause a significant increase in stopping distance, leading to accidents and putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal extends to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal has a delayed response
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.
